This paper discusses the selection of the best classification algorithm for a given dataset, which is a common problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the properties of different measures used to assess classification performance, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CV (Computer Vision) depending on the specific application. Additionally, the paper may be relevant to researchers in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) who are interested in classification tasks.
